Install Ubuntu:

Java 8 install ubuntu:

sudo add-apt-repository ppa:webupd8team/java
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install oracle-java8-installer

java -version

		java version "1.8.0_66"
		Java(TM) SE Runtime Environment (build 1.8.0_66-b17)
		Java HotSpot(TM) 64-Bit Server VM (build 25.66-b17, mixed mode)


sudo apt-get install oracle-java8-set-default


Aspectj install:

Download: http://www.eclipse.org/downloads/download.php?file=/tools/aspectj/aspectj-1.8.7.jar&mirror_id=17    (now: 1.8.7 release)

Run the jar file.
And open aspectj installation folder in lib folder and  sudo cp * /usr/lib/jvm/java-8-oracle/jre/lib/ext/



